                                                                                        Detecting Web DDoS — Task-Wise Answers

Task 1 — Introduction
• (No direct answers — just room setup)

Task 2 — DoS and DDoS Attacks

2.1 What class of attack relies on disrupting the availability of a web service? → Denial-of-Service
2.2 What do we call the network of compromised machines that attackers use to launch DDoS attacks? → Botnet

Task 3 — Attack Motives

3.1 Which attacker motive aims to make customers lose confidence in a company? → Reputational Damage
3.2 Which motive most likely drove the 2023 DDoS attack against Microsoft? → Hacktivism

Task 4 — Log Analysis

4.1 What is the attacker’s IP address? → 203.12.23.195
4.2 Which page is repeatedly targeted by the attacker’s requests? → /login
4.3 After the attack, what error code do legitimate users receive? → 503

Task 5 — Leveraging SIEMs

5.1 What was the most frequently requested URI? → /search
5.2 Which clientip made the most requests to the target URI? → 203.0.113.7
5.3 How many IP addresses were part of the botnet that attacked your website? → 60
5.4 Which user-agent was most commonly used by the attacking traffic? → Java/1.8.0_181
5.5 What is the peak number of requests made per second during the attack? → 207
5.6 Which legitimate (non-attacking) clientip received the first 503 response status post-attack? → 10.10.0.27

Task 6 — Defense

6.1 What type of security challenge blocks bots by asking users to solve a simple puzzle? → CAPTCHA
6.2 Which CDN feature spreads traffic across multiple servers to prevent overload? → Load-balancing
